{
  "texts": [
    "Example 1: We collected the bulk gene expression data from 26 patients with acute myeloid leukemia (AML) and 38 healthy donors 72.",
    "We calculated the TF activity for these samples based on the LINGER-inferred cell population GRN from PBMCs and found that FOXN1 is significantly less active in patients with AML than in healthy donors, and it is not differentially expressed (Fig. 6a, b).",
    "In addition, we calculated the TF activity of the transcriptome profile (bulk RNA-seq data) of 671 individuals with AML 73 and performed survival analysis, which indicated that individuals with high FOXN1 activity level tend to have a higher survival probability (Fig. 6c).",
    "Furthermore, FOXN1 has been reported as a tumor suppressor 74.",
    "Example 2: We also present an example of the naive CD4 + T cell response upon T cell receptor (TCR) stimulation 75, which induces T cell differentiation into various effector cells and activates T lymphocytes."
  ]
}